==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cheeseflower
<hw>cheeseflower</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an erect or decumbent Old World
perennial (<spn>Malva sylvestris</spn>) with axillary clusters of
rosy-purple flowers; introduced into the U. S.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tall mallow, high mallow, cheese, <spn>Malva
sylvestris</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

